This test case conducts offline calculation of radiation scheme using input data. Below variables are required for calculation as input data. The data format of input data is 4-byte binary (grads format).

---------------------------------------------------
variable,   file name,            coordinate
---------------------------------------------------
DENS        input/DENS.grd        model level(3D)
RHOT        input/RHOT.grd        model level(3D)
TEMP        input/T.grd           model level(3D)
PRES        input/PRES.grd        model level(3D)
QV          input/QV.grd          model level(3D)
QC          input/QC.grd          model level(3D)
QR          input/QR.grd          model level(3D)
QI          input/QI.grd          model level(3D)
QS          input/QS.grd          model level(3D)
QG          input/QG.grd          model level(3D)
SFC_TEMP    input/SFC_TEMP.grd    surface(2D)
SFC_ALB_LW  input/SFC_ALB_LW.grd  surface(2D)
SFC_ALB_SW  input/SFC_ALB_SW.grd  surface(2D)
---------------------------------------------------


1) Prepare input data for a radiation scheme. You can use sample programs in "input" directory.

   input/get_inputdata.sh
   input/make_grads_file.f90

If you use these sample programs, the history file (history.peXXXXXX.nc) must not include output data in boundary region. Namely, please set "HIST_BND" to "false" in run.conf when the calculation for preparing input data were conducted.

&PARAM_HIST
 HIST_BND = .false.,
/


2) Set below parameters of run.conf and init.conf in this directory according to your input data format. 

&PARAM_INDEX
 KMAX 
 IMAX 
 JMAX 
/

&PARAM_GRID
 DX 
 DY 
 FZ(:) or DZ
/

&PARAM_ATMOS
  ATMOS_PHY_RD_TYPE = "MSTRNX",  or "WRF",
/

&PARAM_MAPPROJ
 MPRJ_basepoint_lon
 MPRJ_basepoint_lat
/

&PARAM_USER
 USER_do   = .true.,
 ITIME     = 1,        #<- record numbar of input data you want to use
/

